Khenari oral tradition preserves the rite's failure as the moment when living solar law and dead underworld law ceased to be one system and became two incompatible authorities occupying the same space — the literal embodiment of jurisdictional conflict with no arbitration mechanism.
Ushabti tradition preserves the Meridian Intake March's administrative records as evidence of what the administrative tradition looked like before the Twin Sovereign period's doctrinal overwriting corrupted it — the Keeper intake-gate system as an example of pure administrative function before theological competition contaminated it.

