Ushabti relationship to the Scorched Wastes is specific and painful: the Meridian Intake March was one of the clearest expressions of the administrative tradition Ushabti carry as cultural identity — an intake system managing movement, certification, and legal status through documented procedure rather than armed coercion.
The Twin Sovereign period's overwriting of intake-gate function with funerary jurisdiction claims is, in Ushabti legal reading, the moment the administrative system was corrupted at its root: the intake gate was made to ask "does this traveler fall under dead jurisdiction?" instead of "does this traveler have proper documentation?"
The Ninth Meridian Rite's failure and the subsequent undead administrative persistence — revenants still issuing ration decrees — is the Ushabti nightmare scenario: institutional authority that has outlasted its legitimacy source, continuing through procedural momentum without accountability, enforcing rules no living authority can revoke because the enforcement mechanism is itself undead.

