Khenari death-rite geography in the Scorched Wastes identifies the site of the Rite's failure as a location where the living and dead jurisdictions collapsed into each other in a way that violated both.
The proper function of funerary geography — marking a boundary between living movement and dead territory, maintaining separate but adjacent authorities — was destroyed when Moon-aligned functionaries tried to impose funerary jurisdiction on an active caravan corridor.
The Rite's failure produced the specific outcome Khenari death-rite geography is designed to prevent: the dead and living occupying the same space without the jurisdictional separation that keeps both safe.
The undead administrative persistence — revenants issuing Keeper-period ration decrees — is not merely a practical hazard in Khenari reading but a cosmological wrong: dead authorities should not issue living-world administrative commands.
The Wastes are a sacred warning site as much as a dangerous terrain.
